{"serial": "43040", "department_serial": 39, "code": "IMA010", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Financial Management in E-Commerce", "ch": "電子商務財務管理"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["CHIU,HSIN-YU"], "ch": ["邱信瑜"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 6, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "I1", "room": "404"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "資訊管理學系", "en": "Department of Information Management"}, "system": {"ch": "碩士在職專班", "en": "Master Programme (Adult Learning)"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 38, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程介紹財務管理的意涵及基本觀念, 協助同學理解企業中財務管理的重要性及實際操作. 課程將涵蓋財報分析, 證券評價, 資本市場及企業的資本預算和資本結構. 預期學生在課程結束能夠針對企業的財務管理議題有所認知並提出解決方案.", "en": "This course introduces the implications and fundamental concepts of financial management, assisting students in understanding the importance and practical applications of financial management within enterprises. The course covers financial statement analysis, securities valuation, capital markets, and corporate capital budgeting and structure. It is expected that students will develop an awareness of financial management issues within enterprises and propose solutions by the end of the course."}, "outline": {"ch": "1. 財務管理簡介\n2. 財務報表, 稅及現金流量\n3. 時間價值及折現\n4. 債券及股票評價\n5. 資本預算\n6. 資本市場, 風險及報酬\n7. 資本結構及股利政策\n8. 營運資金管理", "en": "1.Introduction to Financial Management\n2.Financial Statements, Taxation, and Cash Flows\n3.Time Value of Money and Discounting\n4.Bond and Stock Valuation\n5.Capital Budgeting\n6.Capital Markets, Risk, and Return\n7.Capital Structure and Dividend Policy\n8.Working Capital Management"}, "textbook": {"ch": "“Essentials of Corporate Finance“, 11th ed. Ross, Westerfield, and Jordan", "en": "“Essentials of Corporate Finance“, 11th ed. Ross, Westerfield, and Jordan"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "50", "en": "50"}, "instructMeth